			<ns0:name>mcgra...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/100177598732114324016/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Since we don't have the normal filesystem mount distinctions anyway,
I think a good choice is --prefix= (i.e. blank), which puts everything
in /lib and /share and so on.  That keeps the names as short as they can be
while still having the canonical structure.  In the NaCl context we gain
nothing I can think of from the /usr vs / distinction.
